{
  "texts": [
    "In such cases, supervised models may become less reliable.",
    "To address these challenges, researchers have turned to other learning approaches.",
    "Complementing these approaches, semi-supervised learning enhances model robustness by integrating a small set of labeled data with a larger pool of unlabeled data.",
    "Notably, Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) generate synthetic data to augment limited datasets in flavor research, improving model training and validation (Queiroz et al. 2023).",
    "Beyond data augmentation, generative models are increasingly being used for direct taste simulation."
  ]
}